title: WHAT WE OFFER
texts: To make quality education accessible, the board provides merit and need-based scholarship opportunities

At the AKU Examination Board (AKU-EB), we believe every learner deserves an education that prepares them not just for exams, but for life. Our programmes are designed to nurture critical thinking, creativity, and a sense of responsibility — empowering students to thrive in a rapidly changing world. We are committed to helping learners become informed, capable, and compassionate global citizens, contributing to

Students pursuing Secondary School Certificate (SSC) in Grades 9 and 10, access a broad range of subjects over two years, gaining a deep understanding of key academic concepts and explore their interest in various fields of studies. The Higher Secondary School Certificate (HSSC) for Grades 11 and 12 concludes the final years of secondary education. It focuses on advanced knowledge, academic rigour, and preparation for higher education and lifelong learning.​

AKU-EB is more than an examination board — it's a partner in your child's growth and success. Through our innovative programmes, we don't just educate; we inspire students to become leaders, problem-solvers, and change-makers who can contribute meaningfully to their communities and to the world.

Our academic journey begins with the Primary School Programme (PSP) for Grades 4 and 5, where students build strong foundations in literacy, numeracy, and ethical values. This continues with our Middle School Programme (MSP) for Grades 6 to 8 — a project-based, experiential learning​ model that encourages curiosity, real-world problem solving, and the development of essential 21st Century Skills. Both programmes lay a strong foundation for students' successful​ transition into secondary and higher secondary education.

title: ABOUT US
texts: Diversity and pluralism are instituted in AKU-EB's core philosophy. Today, the Examination Board strives towards achieving inclusiveness in all its programmes and aims to deliver an education that can be experienced by all citizens irrespective of their ethnicity, gender, religion or disability.​
To increase access to quality education for lower and middle income students at a secondary and higher secondary school level
To be a model of excellence and innovation in education for Pakistan and the developing world
To inculcate a culture of higher order thinking in the youth through indigenous educational development and assessment programmes

AKU-EB’s syllabi are based on the national curriculum of Pakistan and are aimed at being accessible to both English and Urdu medium schools. Furthermore, AKU-EB’s examination system is intended to function within bot​h the public and private spheres of Pakistani educati​on. It represents an indigenous educational movement created for Pakistani students, with an emphasis on concept based learning and a conscious rejection of rote memorization that plagues many Pakistani schools today.
To acquire new knowledge through research and share best practices in education

​The Aga Khan University Examination Board (AKU-EB) is a Pakistan based examination and education system that was established in 2002​ by Aga Khan University, in accordance with Ordinance CXIV of the Government of Pakistan. The system covers four separate programmes of education: The Primary School Programme (PSP), the Middle School Programme (MSP), the Secondary School Certificate (SSC) and the Higher Secondary School Certificate (HSSC). Together, these four programmes account for a student’s instruction from Grade 4 up till and including Grade 12, after ​which they may pursue higher education.​

title: WHAT WE DO
texts: AKU-EB offers a number of unique services that help facilitate students towards resources aimed at helping to create a rich educational experience.

AKU-EB also works with students and schools in coming up with individually tailored solutions towards any hinderances that they might face. In doing so, we aim to provide all necessary support towards overcoming geographic and logistical obstacles.

Anthologies and past papers can be requested by students or teachers via forms that can be downloaded from our website, whilst new Syllabi CDs are sent for free to all affiliated schools and to others on request. Additionally, students can use our website to view subject syllabi, pass on individual queries or concerns, view results online, request duplicate admissions cards, and correct any errors in their registered information on our website.

Learning Support Materials are supplementary services offered by AKU-EB to assist students. These resources include past papers for all subjects, anthologies for Urdu Compulsory, Urdu Asaan and English Literature subjects, a guide for SSC I English Compulsory, resource lists and concept maps for ten subjects, and a command words guide.

title: MIDDLE SCHOOL PROGRAMME (MSP)
texts: The AKU-EB Middle School Programme (MSP) is a project based experiential form of learning that places an emphasis on interdisciplinary learning through the application of knowledge in real world situations. The programme serves as a strong foundation upon which students can prepare for their progress to the SSC and HSSC programmes.

MSP focuses on developing a 21st century skillset among students that includes competencies such as, Creativity and Innovation, Critical Thinking and Problem Solving, Interpersonal Skills and Teamwork. These skills are deemed vital to success in both school years and beyond.​​

title: SECONDARY SCHOOL CERTIFICATE (SSC)
texts: AKU-EB offers a choice of fifteen elective subjects at the SSC level. Students are required to take examinations for five compulsory and three elective subjects over a period of two years.

AKU-EB SSC syllabi offers an excellent foundation for higher secondary education and beyond. The syllabi are offered in both English and Urdu, comprising of achievable Student Learning Outcomes (SLOs) that encourage conceptual learning and develop higher order cognitive skills.​

title: HIGHER SECONDARY SCHOOL CERTIFICATE (HSSC)
texts: AKU-EB HSSC offers a strong platform to students for success in university education and professional life. It emphasizes on application of conceptual learning and further development of higher order cognitive skills, hence preparing students for success in the 21st century.
HSSC students are required to undertake examinations for four compulsory and three elective subjects over a period of two years.

title: EDUCATIONAL DEVELOPMENT
texts: AKU-EB views assessment as only being one component of the greater whole of its educational philosophy. Our long-term aim in the development of education in Pakistan is to include improved teacher development and resources, improve the overall quality of education received by students in Pakistan and making both secondary and higher secondary education accessible to lower and middle income students.

The AKU-EB philosophy places a premium on concept based learning with experiential practices, testing students on their understanding and application of learned concepts rather than regurgitating them ad verbatim. This also leads to an emphasis being placed on critical thinking and reasoning skills, with a culture of independent research and intellectual curiosity driving our students in their pursuits. Valuable life skills such as teamwork, responsibility, listening/observation skills and communication skills are also imparted.

We strive to ensure inclusiveness in all of our programmes, aiming to deliver an educational experience that does not discriminate against citizens based on ethnicity, gender, religion or disability.​​​​

In  addition, we host and organize an interactive endeavor to assist school heads, principals and institutional leaders across Pakistan to connect and assist one another in matters of institutional development, knowledge transfer and school improvement programmes, known as the “Principals’ Network”.

title: SCHOLARSHIP PROGRAMMES
texts: ​​The AKU-EB recognizes the vital importance of the bridge between secondary and higher education. Thanks to the generous assistance of the Fancy Foundation, AKU-EB offers a competitive scholarship that contributes towards expenses incurred by students during their two years as HSSC candidates. The scholarship is awarded on the basis of merit and financial need and funds two years of education for students that aim to complete their HSSC from an AKU-EB affiliated school or college. It is offered to current SSC Part II students or SSC graduates of AKU-EB affiliated schools & colle​ges based in Karachi. ​

The scholarship covers up to 3500 rupees of school/college tuition fees per month, an annual book allowance of 2500 rupees per year and full coverage of all AKU-EB examination fees for the two years of ​HSSC. It does not, however, cover uniform, travel and other subsistence costs.

Aside from being AKU-EB SSC students, potential applicants for the scholarship must have obtained a minimum of 70% marks overall, have no failing grades in either year of their SSC examinations and must demonstrate personal qualities such as a commitment to social service, adaptability and leadership skills.​​

title: AFFILIATION
texts: Schools will be evaluated according to a number of criteria that AKU-EB's Quality Assurance team must be satisfied are being fulfilled. For example, the physical premises of the school should be sufficiently clean, have due safety procedures for both students and staff, provide necessary spaces such as science laboratories and libraries (which must also be properly equipped according to AKU-EB specifications), and should also have audio equipment capable of sufficient amplification for classroom use.
Investigations by AKU-EB, as prompted by suspicious circumstances either being reported by the school itself or AKU-EB's internal quality control procedure, must be complied with fully.

Staff at affiliated schools must have relevant qualifications in the subjects that they teach. All teachers engaged in the teaching of AKU-EB syllabi must have a copy of the relevant subject syllabus and, if required, should receive training that will be provided by AKU-EB. Schools should also be prepared to provide all reasonable access to teaching space, students and teachers to authorized representatives of AKU-EB.

In order for a school to become affiliated with the Aga Khan University Examination Board, the institution must follow a series application, review and approval procedures as set by the AKU-EB Board of Directors. Affiliation will be renewed annually, subject to compliance with the procedures set forward by AKU-EB; affiliated schools can and will be subject to visits and reviews that ensure this compliance.

There are several categories of affiliation that can be awarded to schools, depending on AKU-EB's evaluation of the school's capabilities in meeting the requirements for both preparing candidates for AKU-EB examinations and potentially even conducting AKU-EB examinations themselves.

title: PRINCIPALS' NETWORK
texts: Through the use of an institutional G Suite for Education, members of the network will be able to stay connected and enjoy a variety of services free of cost such as Google Classroom, Gmail, Drive, Calendar, Docs, Sheets, Slides, Sites, Hangouts and much more.

The Principals' Network is an endeavor designed and initiated by the Aga Khan University Examination Board (AKU-EB) for principals of affiliated as well as non-affiliated schools. The network aims to engage school principals, heads and institutional leaders across Pakistan and facilitate the transfer of knowledge and experiences needed for the development and implementation of whole school improvement programmes.

Under the network, multiple events will be held throughout the year to promote effective linkages amongst principals and help build advice-seeking ties that are mutually beneficial for all members. As a result, principals will be able to discuss their challenges, receive relevant advice, share best practices and come up with effective solutions to persisting problems.
Development of capacity through need-based interventions;
Exposure to best practices through online talks and seminars and much more.​​​
Transforming the role of a principal as a pedagogical leader and an agent of change;
Development of a more social / collaborative view towards teaching and learning;
Focused discussions on challenges faced by school principals;
The network will also offer additional flexibility for members to interact, share experiences and concerns, and engage in discussion on specific topics in an informal setting through Facebook.​​

title: SERVICES
texts: Part of what makes AKU-EB’s approach to education unique is that creating syllabi and conducting examinations comprise only one part of our relationship with affiliated schools. In addition to these facilities, we also offer several services that schools and students may avail themselves of.
Our goal with these services is to present an approach examination board that supports both students and schools in matters of logistics and problem solving.​

Our website also contains a number of PDF forms that both students and schools can use to order learning support materials such as past papers and learning DVDs, correct their personal information details, request duplicate admissions cards and essentially access a one window service that connects them directly to AKU-EB without needing to go through a third party.

School Affiliation, E-Enrollment, Online Results and School Profiles are all online services that schools can use both to apply for AKU-EB affiliation, to register students for examination sessions and to view results for examinations online; online results can also be accessed by individual students in order to view their own results. We also provide all of our affiliated schools with a School Performance Report following each examination period, which represents AKU-EB’s assessment of the school’s performance for the examination session.

title: LEARNING MATERIALS
texts: The variety of our materials ensures that students across Pakistan are not hampered on the basis of their geographical location, gender or socio-economic status. Standard examples here include access to past papers from the AKU-EB system and syllabi that detail our learning expectations, outcomes and reading material.

In some cases, learning materials help overcome a particular obstacle that students may face. For example, our English Literature and Urdu anthologies ensure that all reading material specified by the national curriculum’s requirements is found in one location, rather than forcing our students to purchase multiple books for the sake of keeping up with the syllabus.​

Aga Khan University Examination Board invests heavily in learning materials because of our belief that they are central to the inquiry-based model of learning that we follow. These materials facilitate the implementation of our ​​syllabi and also create common ground for students, teachers and our examiners to base both learning and assessment goals on.
